# basic PAM auth for Alpine — steelhead override of /usr/lib/pam.d/base-auth.
#
# Identical to the Alpine base-auth EXCEPT the two "-auth optional" desktop
# keyring lines are dropped. On this headless/appliance device every login is
# key-based ssh (no login password), so pam_gnome_keyring's login-keyring
# unlock always failed and logged "gkr-pam: couldn't unlock the login keyring"
# on EVERY ssh session. gnome-keyring is a hard dependency of
# nm-applet/gvfs/webkit (can't be removed) and nothing here uses the user
# keyring (NM secrets live in system-connections), so dropping it from the
# auth stack is correct, not a mask. Only base-auth is shadowed — base-session
# (pam_systemd / XDG_RUNTIME_DIR) is left untouched deliberately.
#
# NB: this mirrors the Alpine base-auth as of the pmOS snapshot; if Alpine's
# /usr/lib/pam.d/base-auth gains a new required module, re-sync this file.
auth required pam_unix.so nullok
auth required pam_nologin.so
auth required pam_env.so
